<body>
<header>
  <h1>1. Division of Ancient History and Sources</h1>
</header>

<div class="container">
<div class="chapter">

<h2>📅 3 Divisions of History</h2>
<div class="timeline">
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <b>History</b><br>
    Written evidences available<br>
    From Vedic Phase till present
  </div>
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <b>Prehistory</b><br>
    No written evidence<br>
    Archaeological evidences available<br>
    Stone age
  </div>
  <div class="timeline-item">
    <b>Proto-history</b><br>
    Written evidences available<br>
    But could not be deciphered<br>
    Eg. Harappan Period
  </div>
</div>

<div class="fact-box">
<b>Key Idea:</b> History is all about understanding the past. Sources are crucial to unravel and understand the past.
</div>

<h2>📚 Sources of History - Tap to Flip</h2>
<div class="flip-grid">
  <div class="flip-card">
    <div class="flip-inner">
      <div class="flip-front">Archaeological Evidence</div>
      <div class="flip-back">Artefacts - materials used by ancient people found at sites. Tools, pottery, burials, settlements, architectural remains.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="flip-card">
    <div class="flip-inner">
      <div class="flip-front">Inscriptions</div>
      <div class="flip-back">Engravings on stone or metal objects. Rock edicts, pillar edicts. Study = Epigraphy【260126083628465904245†L17-L19】</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="flip-card">
    <div class="flip-inner">
      <div class="flip-front">Coins</div>
      <div class="flip-back">Study of coins = Numismatics【260126083628465904245†L20-L21】. First to issue gold coins: Indo-Greek king Menander【163414863101167980797†L19-L22】</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="flip-card">
    <div class="flip-inner">
      <div class="flip-front">Literature</div>
      <div class="flip-back">Indian + Foreign literature. Vedas, Puranas, Epics, Sangam literature, plays【260126083628465904245†L24-L36】</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="flip-card">
    <div class="flip-inner">
      <div class="flip-front">Foreign Accounts</div>
      <div class="flip-back">Magasthenes, Ptolemy, Pliny, Fa-Hien, Hiuen Tsang etc. Records of admin, trade, society【260126083628465904245†L38-L88】</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<details open>
<summary>Literature Sources - All Facts</summary>

<b>A. Indian Literature:</b>
<ul>
<li><span class="key-term">Vedic Literature:</span> Vedas, Brahmanas, Aranyakas, Upanishads, Vedangas and Upvedas【260126083628465904245†L26-L28】</li>
<li><span class="key-term">Puranas:</span> Stories of kings and gives genealogies of dynasties. Important source for political history【260126083628465904245†L29-L31】</li>
<li><span class="key-term">Epics:</span> Ramayana, Mahabharata【260126083628465904245†L32-L33】</li>
<li><span class="key-term">Sangam Literature:</span> Tolkappiyam, Ettuogai, Pattupattu, Pathinenkilkanakku, Silpadikarm and Manimekkalai【260126083628465904245†L33-L35】</li>
<li><span class="key-term">Plays:</span> by Kalidas; Navaratnas in court of Guptas【260126083628465904245†L36-L37】</li>
</ul>

<b>B. Foreign Literature:</b>
<table>
<tr><th>Author</th><th>Book</th><th>Subject</th></tr>
<tr><td>Magasthenes (Greek)</td><td>Indica</td><td>Admin + socio-economic conditions of Mauryas【260126083628465904245†L40-L45】</td></tr>
<tr><td>Ptolemy (Greek)</td><td>Geography of India</td><td>Geographical treatise on India in 2nd Century AD【260126083628465904245†L47-L52】</td></tr>
<tr><td>Pliny (Greek)</td><td>Naturakus Historia</td><td>Trade relations between Rome and India in 1st Century AD【260126083628465904245†L54-L59】</td></tr>
<tr><td>Anonymous (Greek)</td><td>Periplus of Erythrean Sea</td><td>Records personal voyage of Indian coasts in 80 A.D【260126083628465904245†L60-L66】</td></tr>
<tr><td>Fa-Hien (Chinese)</td><td>Record of Buddhist Countries (Fo-Kuoki)</td><td>Records Gupta Empire in 5th Century AD【260126083628465904245†L69-L76】</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hiuen Tsang (Chinese)</td><td>Si-Yu-Ki</td><td>Social, economic, religious conditions of India 5th-7th Century AD, Harshvardhan【260126083628465904245†L78-L88】</td></tr>
<tr><td>I-tsing (Chinese)</td><td>Record of Buddhist religion</td><td>Studies Gupta period under Sri Gupta in 7th Century AD【260126083628465904245†L90-L102】</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hwuili (Chinese)</td><td>Life of Hiuen Tsang</td><td>Accounts Hiuen Tsang's travel in India【260126083628465904245†L104-L109】</td></tr>
</table>

<b>C. Other:</b>
<ul>
<li>Visakha Datta: Mudra Rakshas - Gupta period, Chanakya-Chandragupta story【260126083628465904245†L112-L113】</li>
</ul>
</details>

<details>
<summary>Archaeological Evidences - Details</summary>
<ul>
<li><b>Artefacts:</b> materials used by ancient people found at sites, useful to understand pre-historic Period【250304738559741122874†L9-L11】</li>
<li><b>Tools:</b> stone and bone tools and tools made up of metals like Bronze and Iron【250304738559741122874†L12-L13】</li>
<li><b>Pottery:</b> Black and Red Ware, Northern Black polished ware, Polished Grey Ware etc【250304738559741122874†L14-L15】</li>
<li><b>Inscriptions:</b> Engravings on stone or other metal objects. Rock edicts- Major and Minor and Pillar edicts【250304738559741122874†L19-L21】</li>
<li><b>Important Sites:</b> Bhimbetka - 500 painted Rock Shelters, Mehargarh - Earliest evidence of agriculture, Koldihawa - Earliest evidence of rice【250304738559741122874†L25-L36】</li>
</ul>
</details>

<div class="quiz">
<h4>Quick Check</h4>
<p>Which period has written evidence but it could not be deciphered?</p>
<div class="option">A) History</div>
<div class="option">B) Prehistory</div>
<div class="option">C) Proto-history ← Correct: Eg. Harappan Period【260126083628465904245†L10-L12】</div>
</div>

</div>
